verses.text_plain: It is a good thing to give thanks unto the Lord, and to sing praises unto thy name, O most High:
verses.verse_html: 1It is a good thing to give thanks unto the Lord, and to sing praises unto thy name, O most High:

verses.text_plain: To shew forth thy lovingkindness in the morning, and thy faithfulness every night,
verses.verse_html:
2To shew forth thy lovingkindness in the morning, and thy faithfulness every night, ▼
▼ every…: Heb. in the nights

footnotes.body_html: ▼ every…: Heb. in the nights

verses.text_plain: Upon an instrument of ten strings, and upon the psaltery; upon the harp with a solemn sound.
verses.verse_html:
3Upon an instrument of ten strings, and upon the psaltery; upon the harp with a solemn sound. ▼
▼ the harp…: or, the solemn sound with the harp
 , ▼
▼ a solemn…: Heb. Higgaion

tokens.text: Upon an instrument of ten strings

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the harp…: or, the solemn sound with the harp
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the harp…: or, the solemn sound with the harp
▼ a solemn…: Heb. Higgaion

verses.text_plain: For thou, Lord, hast made me glad through thy work: I will triumph in the works of thy hands.
verses.verse_html: 4For thou, Lord, hast made me glad through thy work: I will triumph in the works of thy hands.

verses.text_plain: O Lord, how great are thy works! and thy thoughts are very deep.
verses.verse_html: 5O Lord, how great are thy works! and thy thoughts are very deep.

verses.text_plain: A brutish man knoweth not; neither doth a fool understand this.
verses.verse_html: 6A brutish man knoweth not; neither doth a fool understand this.

verses.text_plain: When the wicked spring as the grass, and when all the workers of iniquity do flourish; it is that they shall be destroyed for ever:
verses.verse_html: 7When the wicked spring as the grass, and when all the workers of iniquity do flourish; it is that they shall be destroyed for ever:

verses.text_plain: But thou, Lord, art most high for evermore.
verses.verse_html: 8But thou, Lord, art most high for evermore.

verses.text_plain: For, lo, thine enemies, O Lord, for, lo, thine enemies shall perish; all the workers of iniquity shall be scattered.
verses.verse_html: 9For, lo, thine enemies, O Lord, for, lo, thine enemies shall perish; all the workers of iniquity shall be scattered.

verses.text_plain: But my horn shalt thou exalt like the horn of an unicorn: I shall be anointed with fresh oil.
verses.verse_html: 10But my horn shalt thou exalt like the horn of an unicorn: I shall be anointed with fresh oil.

verses.text_plain: Mine eye also shall see my desire on mine enemies, and mine ears shall hear my desire of the wicked that rise up against me.
verses.verse_html: 11Mine eye also shall see my desire on mine enemies, and mine ears shall hear my desire of the wicked that rise up against me.

verses.text_plain: The righteous shall flourish like the palm tree: he shall grow like a cedar in Lebanon.
verses.verse_html: 12The righteous shall flourish like the palm tree: he shall grow like a cedar in Lebanon.

verses.text_plain: Those that be planted in the house of the Lord shall flourish in the courts of our God.
verses.verse_html: 13Those that be planted in the house of the Lord shall flourish in the courts of our God.

verses.text_plain: They shall still bring forth fruit in old age; they shall be fat and flourishing;
verses.verse_html:
14They shall still bring forth fruit in old age; they shall be fat and flourishing; ▼
▼ flourishing: Heb. green

tokens.text: They shall still bring forth fruit

verses.text_plain: To shew that the Lord is upright: he is my rock, and there is no unrighteousness in him.
verses.verse_html: 15To shew that the Lord is upright: he is my rock, and there is no unrighteousness in him.
